verbatimLocality: Montana de Oro State Park, San Luis Obispo, California, United States
occurrenceRemarks: The sea spider Pycnogonum stearnsi feeding on a very small brooding anemone while clutching the nudibranch Aegires albopunctatus. I don't think this sea spider regularly attacks nudibranchs, so I think it was just looking for something to hold on to.

verbatimLocality: Fitzgerald Marine Reserve, Moss Beach, CA
occurrenceRemarks: First sea spider! Ok, not the first, but first pic. I'd read they could be found sucking from the base of anemone columns, so after checking a bunch, I finally found this on a Sola Anemone (Anthopleura sola). Rad!

verbatimLocality: Fitzgerald Marine Reserve, Moss Beach, CA
occurrenceRemarks: Yet another, this time on a Giant Green Anemone (Anthopleura xanthogrammica). This one was slightly bigger, and male, indicated by the presence of the ovigers, egg-carrying legs unique to this class and only present on the males for this family.
